00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:47,960
any other experience. That said, there were daily 
frustrations. There were daily frustrations in  

362
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:54,040
that job, and a lot of it has to do with the fact 
that the PM leader's job is extremely lonely. The  

363
00:38:54,040 --> 00:39:00,360
PM's job, the PM's on your team, their job is 
also lonely. But a PM leader's job is further  

364
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:08,840
lonelier. So there's that. There's also what I 
learned at the time when I started asking this  

365
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:26,040
question is that our jobs get frustrating when we 
behave, most of the time, in misalignment with our  

366
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:35,080
superpowers and who we truly are at our core.
Okay, so for me, as I was evaluating that  

367
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:40,560
question, it's like, "Why am I getting frustrated 
every day? I love the job, I love the macro,  

368
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:51,840
but I do not like the micro. And so why is that?" 
And that's when I actually... There's a simple  

369
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:58,560
framework that I've shared, which is you can be 
doing your work at three levels. Product work  

370
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:02,520
happens at three levels. There's the impact level, 
there's the execution level, and there's the  

371
00:40:02,520 --> 00:40:14,800
optics level. My epiphany as I was exploring this 
question was I have a preferred level at which I  

372
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:22,760
like to operate, but if most of the day, and most 
of the week, and most of the month, I am forcing  

373
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:33,440
myself to operate in not my happy place, in my 
non-default level, that makes me very frustrated. 

374
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:41,720
So many product leaders, their happy place is the 
execution level. In my case, my happy place is the  

375
00:40:41,720 --> 00:40:49,480
impact level. So that is fine. Your happy place 
can be whatever level, it doesn't matter. But the  

376
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:57,560
point is, as you go higher up in the corporate 
ladder, no matter what kind of company it is,  

377
00:40:57,560 --> 00:41:02,720
you are now going to have to spend a lot of 
time on optics, at the optics level. And I have  

378
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:08,280
willpower, I have the skills to do it, I have all 
of that. So it's not about willpower or skills,  

379
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:20,000
but willpower is finite. So as I spent day in and 
day out, just mostly doing optics work, I realized  

380
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:27,240
I was not happy and I was getting frustrated. And 
so that's when I realized the solution, which is  

381
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:34,960
I have to abandon the traditional path, that like, 
"Oh, after this level, I'm supposed to do this,  

382
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:39,160
and then I'm supposed to do this, and then this 
is what society expects. This is what my mom  

383
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:44,920
expects. What will people say on LinkedIn 
when they see my LinkedIn profile?" Like,  

384
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:49,800
"Oh, he has this progression, this, and 
then what stopped? Why did it stop?" 

385
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:55,480
So when I realized this, I said, when a team 
grew to a certain size, so when I was at  

386
00:41:55,480 --> 00:42:00,320
Stripe and I realized this, when the team I was 
managing, it had a fan out of about 50 people,  

387
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:05,720
so this includes engineers and everything, 
